Examples for lesson 2 - Static and dynamic libraries in C/C++

ex1 : Simple example of static library
      Run make and exemple1


ex2 : Example of dynamic library linked at compile time
      Run make, then display and run runit.sh


ex3 : Example of dynamic library link at run time with dl
      Run make, then display and run runit.sh


ex3 : Example of dynamic library linked at run time which contains C++ classes
      Note two different libraries are exchanged !
      Run make, then display and run runit.sh
